## Step 2 — AST parse every .py file under src/
Python's AST parser is the definitive truncation detector — truncated Python
files fail to parse. This catches anything the line counts miss.

    python -c "
    import ast, os, sys
    fails = []
    for r, d, fs in os.walk('src'):
        for f in fs:
            if f.endswith('.py'):
                p = os.path.join(r, f)
                try:
                    ast.parse(open(p, encoding='utf-8').read())
                except SyntaxError as e:
                    fails.append((p, str(e)))
    if fails:
        print('FAILURES:')
        for p, e in fails:
            print(f'  {p}: {e}')
        sys.exit(1)
    else:
        print('All .py files under src/ parse cleanly.')
    "

